Based on the given exercises, the resistance band is initially positioned as follows during an exercise:

* In the Resistance Band Deadlift, Stand on the resistance band with feet shoulder-width apart. Bend at the hips and knees to lift the band off the ground. Therefore, the initial position of the resistance band is on the ground.
* In the Resistance Band Squat, Stand on the resistance band with feet shoulder-width apart. Squat down while holding the band at shoulder height. Therefore, the initial position of the resistance band is around the feet or at shoulder height.
* In the Resistance Band Pull Aparts, Hold the resistance band in front of you with arms extended. Pull the band apart by bringing your hands out to your sides. Therefore, the initial position of the resistance band is in front of the body at arms' length.
* In the Resistance Band Chest Press, Attach the resistance band to a sturdy anchor behind you. Press the handles forward until your arms are fully extended. Therefore, the initial position of the resistance band is attached to the anchor behind the body.
* In the Standing Resistance Band Row, Attach the resistance band to a sturdy anchor. Pull the handles towards your torso, keeping your elbows close to your body. Therefore, the initial position of the resistance band is attached to the anchor.
* In the Band Face Pull, Attach the resistance band to a high anchor. Pull the band towards your face, leading with your elbows. Therefore, the initial position of the resistance band is attached to the anchor at a height above the body.

Considering these exercises, it appears that the initial position of the resistance band can be either:

1. On the ground (Resistance Band Deadlift)
2. Around the feet or at shoulder height (Resistance Band Squat)
3. In front of the body (Resistance Band Pull Aparts)
4. Attached to an anchor (Resistance Band Chest Press, Standing Resistance Band Row, Band Face Pull)

Please note that position may vary depending on the specific exercise and the individual's comfort and flexibility.
